pdnAtmfM4ExtMIB.description: This MIB Module extends the ATM-FORUM-SNMP-M4-MI defined in the Atm Forums M4 Mib

PdnAtmfM4TestErrorCode.name: PdnAtmfM4TestErrorCode
PdnAtmfM4TestErrorCode.description: The specific error codes related to attempting to run a test. The codes have the following meanings: noError(0) -- No Error Occurred badIfIndex(1) -- Specified interface does not exist noVccFound(2) -- The Vcc does not exist on the interface notOwner(3) -- Not the current owner of the test noResourceAvailable(4) -- Device memory allocation failure noLoopbackAllocated(5) -- Could not start the test testCompleted(6) -- Test completed or stopped normally testTimeOut(7) -- Test unsuccessfully due to timeout adminStatusDisabled(8) -- ifAdminStatus is Disabled

pdnAtmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSegMultiCell.name: pdnAtmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSegMultiCell
pdnAtmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSegMultiCell.description: This identifies an OAM Loopback Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using a segment OAM cell. The test type must have appended to it a code that uniquely identifies an intermediate point responsible for looping back the cell. If this is absent, the loopback is performed at the end of the segment or connection. E.g., the OID { pdnAtmfM4TestOAMLoopbackSegMultiCell 5 } identifies that the loopback should be performed at the intermediate point labeled 5.

pdnAtmfM4VcLoopbackTestTable.name: pdnAtmfM4VcLoopbackTestTable

pdnAtmfM4VcLoopbackTestCellsSent.description: This object specifies a count of the number of test cells that have been sent. The value of this object stops increasing when it reaches its maximum value.
